[Term]
id: OGMS:0000085
name: pain
def: "A bodily process in an organism S involving two integrated levels: (a) activation of the nociceptive system and associated emotion generating brain components of S, and (b) a simultaneous aversive sensory and emotional experience on the part of S, where (b) is phenomenologically similar to the sort of aversive experience involved in pain with concordant tissue damage." []
is_a: OGMS:0000020 ! symptom
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Albert Goldfain" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "http://www.referent-tracking.com/RTU/sendfile/?file=painTokyo1_27_2011.pdf" xsd:string
