id: OHD:0010179
name: periodontal pain due to genetic disorder
def: "Periodontal pain due to periodontitis as a manifestion of a systematic genetic disorder. Genetic disorders which can result in periodontitis include familial and cyclic neutropenia, Down syndrome, leukocyte adhesion deficiency syndromes, Papillon–Lefèvre syndrome, Chediak–Higashi syndrome, histiocytosis syndromes, glycogen storage disease, infantile genetic agranulocytosis, Cohen syndrome, Ehler–Danlos syndrome (types IV and VIII), and hypophosphatasia." []
