[Term]
id: OHD:0010272
name: neurovascular orofacial pain
def: "Attacks of variable duration of moderate or severe intraoral pain, without head pain, often accompanied by toothache-like symptoms, with mild autonomic and/or migrainous symptoms. Two subforms are represented by patients with relatively short attacks (1–4 hours) and those with longer attacks (>4 hours)." []
comment: ICOP number: 5.4
