id: UBERON:0008266
name: periodontal ligament
def: "The fibrous connective tissue that surrounds the root of a tooth, separating it from and attaching it to the alveolar bone. It extends from the base of the gingival mucosa to the fundus of the bony socket, and its main function is to hold the tooth in its socket[BTO]." [BTO:0001020, https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1233, https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/21, Wikipedia:Periodontal_fiber]
